- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal methods for computing branching distances between labeled transition systems. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper uses quantitative games to define branching distances. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a possible category as the paper discusses methods for solving path-building games. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) could be a possible category as the paper deals with formal methods for analyzing the behavior of programs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could also be a possible category as the paper discusses methods for computing distances between states in a system, which is a common problem in AI.
